ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC CORR <options> ; 
    BY variables ; 
    FREQ variable ; 
    ID variables ; 
    PARTIAL variables ; 
    VAR variables ; 
    WEIGHT variable ; 
    WITH variables ;

The CORR procedure computes Pearson correlation coefficients, three nonparametric 
measures of association, and the probabilities associated with these statistics. 
The correlation statistics include the following: 

  o Pearson product-moment correlation 
  o Spearman rank-order correlation 
  o Kendall’s tau-b coefficient 
  o Hoeffding’s measure of dependence, D
  o Pearson, Spearman, and Kendall partial correlation
